  <description type="morphology">Stems  long-creeping, 2--3 mm diam.  Leaves  clustered, erect, 0.4--1(--1.3) × 0.1--0.3 m.  Petiole  straw-colored to brown, darker at base, dull, ca. 1/2 length of blade, pubescent with soft, jointed hairs.  Blade  yellow-green or pale green, dull, lanceolate, 2-pinnate-pinnatifid, ca. 3 times as long as wide, base slightly narrowed but truncate, apex acuminate, with soft, silver-gray, jointed hairs on both surfaces.  Basal segments  of pinnules opposite; ultimate segments ovate to lanceolate, base equilateral, truncate, margins deeply lobed, serrate-crenate.  Sori  globose to almost cylindric; indusia tubular to cylindric.  Spores  trilete, globose with low, tuberculate, distal face and equatorial flange. 2 n  = 68.</description>
